It pings a little strange to me that the majority of the staff affected by the event would request to be killed because they were blinded. I find it really hard to believe the Foundation would agree to what is essentially a mass euthanasia of trained staff for a disability that people in reality live with on a daily basis. Unless I'm wildly misinterpreting your usage of the word 'termination' here, I'd encourage you to try to rework the final lines so as to not accidentally imply that being blind is a fate worse than death.







